table-reference.title: List of amendments - NCC 20225 Volume One

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: An “Introduction to this Part” has been added to introduce the intent and purpose of every Part of the NCC.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: The Objectives and Functional Statements have been relocated from the Guide to Volume One into NCC Volume One.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: A number of provisions have been amended, restructured, deleted and relocated as part of the initiative to provide a consistent NCC structure and improve NCC usability.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: A new clause added to specify scope of NCC Volume One.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: A new clause added to specify scope of NCC Volume Two.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: A new clause added to specify scope of NCC Volume Three.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: A Note has been included to outline transitional arrangements regarding new numbering system and documentary evidence.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: A new clause added to limit lead content in copper alloy plumbing products in contact with drinking water.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: A new clause added to require a NatHERS certificate be issued for the house energy rating software output where house energy rating software is required.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: The limitation statement has been amended to include a Class 9b early childhood centre.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: A new sub-clause added to specify non-combustible materials.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

An exemption statement has also been included to provide exemption to certain Class 9b early childhood centres.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: Amended to provide concession for test drain pipes used for fire services.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: Amended to permit use of reports where the tested system differs from the subject system in accordance with AS 4072.1. Also, a new sub-clause has been inserted to clarify that tests must be reported in accordance with Specifications 1 and 2.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: Amended to require each part of storey or fire compartment used as a Class 9b early childhood centre be provided with not less than 2 exits.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: Amended to require stairways or ramps serving Class 9b early childhood centres as a required exit to be fire-isolated. An exemption has been included for certain Class 9b early childhood centres.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: Amended to include new provisions for primary schools. References to early childhood centres have been deleted as a consequence to new and amended Deemed-to-Satisfy Provisions and limitation statement located in A6G1, C3D6, D2D3, D2D4, D2D16, D3D19, D3D22, D3D27, E1D11, Specification 17 and E2D20.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: Amended to make reference to new defined term ‘Volume’.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: Amended to require sprinkler protection for buildings containing a Class 9b early childhood centre. An exemption has been included for certain Class 9b early childhood centres.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: Amended to make reference to new defined term ‘Volume’.

row.entry: Amended to make reference to new defined term ‘Volume’.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: Part F1 has been re-named as a consequence of restructuring, includes new external waterproofing Deemed-to-Satisfy Provisions, and group provisions relating to rainwater management and rising damp.

row.xt:author: Lee Liu

row.xt:author: Lee Liu
row.entry: A new Part has been inserted as a consequence of restructuring Part F1 and contains group provisions for wet areas and overflow protection previously contained in NCC 2019 Amdt 1 Part F1. The remaining Parts of Section F have been renumbered accordingly.
